[1]
Date: Fri 7 Nov 2003
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: World Health Organisation, WER and Epidemiological Bulletin,
Disease Outbreak Report, Fri 7 Nov 2003 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don>


Republic of the Congo: suspected acute hemorrhagic fever syndrome
-----------------------------------------------------------------
As of Fri 7 Nov 2003, a total of 12 suspected cases of acute hemorrhagic
fever syndrome including 9 deaths have been reported in the districts of
Mbomo in the Cuvette Ouest Departement.

A Ministry of Health team is in the field to assess the situation and to
collect clinical samples for diagnosis. These will be tested by the
Institute de Recherches pour le Developpement (IRD) at the Centre
International de Recherches Médicales de Franceville (CIRMF), Gabon.

A National Coordination Committee to contain the outbreak has been
established in Brazzaville under the Direction Generale de la Sante,
assisted by WHO and other international partners.

--
Marianne Hopp
<mjhopp12@yahoo.com>

