[The death toll has risen from 7 to 9 since the first report dated 31 Oct
2003. Dr Dudley has added the comment that the species of suid which was
the presumptive source of the infection is unclear from this report;
possibilities include the giant forest hog _Hylochoerus meinertzhageni_ and
the bush pig _Potamochoerus larvatus_. - Mod.CP]
